    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Save That Seat'' (editorial, June 5), about seats on commuter trains, refers to ''extra-large people with shopping bags roaming the aisle like a flotilla of fat-bottomed boats.'' That's a cheap shot.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Save That Seat'' (editorial, June 5), about seats on commuter trains, refers to ''extra-large people with shopping bags roaming the aisle like a flotilla of fat-bottomed boats.'' That's a cheap shot.</p>
        <p>If God had meant everyone to be thin, she'd have made us taller.</p>
        <p>Marie Shear  Brooklyn, June 5, 2005</p>
      </block>
